msgid "Ticket-Templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../zammad-ticket-templates.rst:4
msgid ""
"If agents need to create tickets with similar content, they can be stored as"
" ticket templates, in order to accelerate the ticketing process in the "
"future. The following ticket information can be put into a template: ticket "
"type, customer, title, text, group, owner, status, priority and tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../zammad-ticket-templates.rst:7
msgid ""
"You can access the templates by clicking on the paper icon, as shown in the "
"following figure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../zammad-ticket-templates.rst:11
msgid ""
"In order to create a new template just enter the required information and "
"choose a matching name, which can be entered in the field “save as "
"template”. Now you can simply choose the template when creating a ticket."
msgstr ""

#: ../../zammad-ticket-templates.rst:18
msgid "Email-Templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../zammad-ticket-templates.rst:19
msgid ""
"If entire tickets with similar content are often created, ticket templates "
"can be created. This speeds up ticket creation. Ticket templates can contain"
" the following information: ticket type, customer, title, test, group, "
"owner, status, priority and tags. The templates can be accessed via the "
"letter icon as shown in the following picture:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../zammad-ticket-templates.rst:25
msgid ""
"Here you can either select an already created template or save the current "
"one under a desired name. When you create a new template, all the required "
"information is entered in the ticket and an appropriate name is selected, "
"which is entered in the field \"Save as template\". After clicking on "
"\"Save\", the template can be selected during the future ticketing process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../zammad-ticket-templates.rst:30
msgid "The templates are available for all agents."
